The '''Goldschmidt School''' was a school that existed in [[Berlin, Germany]] in the 1930s. It was founded by [[Leonore Goldschmidt]], a [[German people|German]] [[Jew]] after Jews were banned from enrolling in German schools.<ref name=Rimer>{{cite news|last=Rimer|first=Sara|title=REUNION RECALLS SCHOOL FOR JEWS IN NAZI GERMANY|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/11/11/nyregion/reunion-recalls-school-for-jews-in-nazi-germany.html|accessdate=2 January 2014|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|date=11 November 1985}}</ref> [[Stella Goldschlag]], who passed as [[Aryan]] and betrayed Jews during the war, was a pupil of the school.<ref name=USHMM>{{cite web|title=Pupils at Goldschmidt School|url=http://www.ushmm.org/online/film/display/detail.php?file_num=4815|publisher=[[United States Holocaust Memorial Museum]]|accessdate=2 January 2014}}</ref> [[Peter H. Wyden]] also attended the school, and later wrote a biography on Goldschlag.<ref name=Abrahamson>{{cite news|last=Abrahamson|first=Irving|title=She Saved Herself In The Holocaust By Betraying Others|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1993-01-03/entertainment/9303150591_1_stella-goldschlag-peter-wyden-berlin|accessdate=2 January 2014|newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=3 January 1993}}</ref>
