This is a '''list of films and TV containing [[corporal punishment]] scenes''', which may be fictional or re-created and include military, prison, domestic, ritual, initiation, judicial and [[Western (genre)|westerns]].
'''1930s''' *''[[Mutiny on the Bounty (1935 film)| Mutiny on the Bounty]]'' (1935). Flogging on board ship. *''[[The Drum (1938 film)| The Drum]]'' (1938). A soldier in the British Army in India is caned with a drumstick. '''1940s''' *''[[Island of Doomed Men]]'' (1940). Sadistic floggings of inmates on a penal island. *''[[How Green Was My Valley (film)| How Green Was My Valley]]'' (1941). A vigourous caning in the schoolyard *''[[Red River (1948 film)| Red River]]'' (1948). A cowboy lashes out at another man with his whip. '''1950s''' *''[[Chain Gang (1950 film)|Chain Gang]]'' (1950). Prisoners endure floggings at the [[whipping post]] and spend time in the [[hot box|sweat box]]. *''[[Against All Flags]]'' (1952). An undercover officer investigating pirates is given 20 lashes on-board ship. *''[[Hellgate (1952 film)|Hellgate]]'' (1952). A prisoner is lashed with a [[cat o'nine tails]]. *''[[Cosh Boy]]'' (1953). A young man is lashed with a belt by his step father. *''[[The Sun Shines Bright]]'' (1953). A dual with buggy whips ends in a thrashing. *''[[The Yellow Balloon (film)| The Yellow Balloon]]'' (1953). A father punishes his son with a belt. *''[[Broken Lance]]'' (1954). An angry cowboy lashes his son with a stock whip. *''[[Gunfight in Abilene|Showdown in Abilene]]'' (1956). Cowboys whip a suspected cattle rustler. *''[[Rebel in Town]]'' (1956). A rebel cowboy ties a man to a tree and whips him until he confesses his crimes. *''[[Jailhouse Rock (film)| Jailhouse Rock]]'' (1957). A prisoner, played by Elvis, is flogged by prison guards. '''1960s''' *''[[Romulus and Remus (1961)| Romulus and Remus]]'' (1961). A man is lashed to a wheel and spun and whipped. *''[[Billy Budd (film)| Billy Budd]]'' (1962). Crew members are flogged on board ship. *''[[H.M.S. Defiant]]'' (1962). The sadistic 1st Lieutenant orders the caning of a midshipman. *''[[Lawrence of Arabia (film)|Lawrence of Arabia]]'' (1962). T. E. Lawrence is thrashed with a cane by his captors. *''[[Mutiny on the Bounty (1962 film)| Mutiny on the Bounty]]'' (1962). A seaman is [[flogged]] for contempt. *''[[Beau Geste (1966 film)|Beau Geste]]'' (1966). The Legionnaire is flogged under the eyes of the sadistic Sergeant Major Dagineau. *''[[Gunfight in Abilene]]'' (1967). A suspected cattle rustler is whipped by cowboys. *''[[The Way West (film)|The Way West]]'' (1967). A US senator leading a wagon train on the Oregon Trail asks his slave to whip his back. *''[[if....]]'' (1968). A trio of students are caned by their peers. *''[[The Charge of the Light Brigade (1968 film)|The Charge of the Light Brigade]]'' (1968). A British Army soldier is tied to a tripod and flogged with a cat o'nine tails. '''1970s''' *''[[Performance (film)|Performance]]'' (1970). A gangster whips a man. *''[[There Was a Crooked Man...]]'' (1970). A convict serving time in an Arizona prison is bound and flogged. *''[[High Plains Drifter]]'' (1973). Various Western whipping scenes. *''[[Midnight Express (film)|Midnight Express]]'' (1978). [[Bastinado]] is administered in a Turkish prison. '''1980s''' *''[[Brubaker]]'' (1980). Guards at an Arkansas prison farm discipline inmates with a heavy leather [[strapping (punishment)|strap]]. *''[[Another Country (film)| Another Country]]'' (1984). A student is caned by his peers. *''[[Full Metal Jacket (film)|Full Metal Jacket]]'' (1987). Recruit Leonard 'Gomer Pyle' Lawerence is given a [[blanket party]] by his fellow soldiers. *''[[Dead Poets Society]]'' (1989). The principal of a New England boarding school disciplines with a [[Paddle (spanking)| paddle]]. *''[[Glory (1989 film)| Glory]]'' (1989). A suspected deserter is bound and lashed in front of his fellow troops. '''1990s''' *''[[Goodfellas]]'' (1990). A gangster recalls the beatings he received from his father with a belt in the 1950s. *''[[The Lawnmower Man (film)| The Lawnmower Man]]'' (1992). Main character is regularly whipped with a leather belt by a Catholic priest. *''[[Unforgiven]]'' (1992). A whipping in a town jail.. *''[[The Cinder Path]]'' (1994). TV movie. A farm worker is forced to crawl along a cinder-covered path by the farm owner. *''[[Starship Troopers (film)| Starship Troopers]]'' (1997). A soldier is bound and flogged. *''[[The Examination for Lieutenant]]'' (1998). Part of the ''[[Hornblower (TV series)| Hornblower]]'' TV series. A seaman turned thief is punished by being forced to run the [[Running the gauntlet| gauntlet]]. *''[[One Man's Hero]]'' (1999). Men of a U.S. Army battalion are lashed for suspected desertion. '''2000s''' *''[[Mr. Deeds]]'' (2002). A father removes his belt and lashes his quarterback son. *''[[Mutiny (2002 film)|Mutiny]]'' (2002). Part of the ''[[Hornblower (TV series)|Hornblower]]'' TV series. A sailor is given 12-of-the-best with a cane onboard ship. *''[[The Sopranos (season 4)| The Sopranos]]'' (2002). Season 4 , Episode 7. Tony repeatedly lashes a man with his belt. *''[[Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World]]'' (2003). A crew member is flogged for refusing to salute a midshipman. *''[[The Proposition (2005 film)| The Proposition]]'' (2005). A outlaw sentenced to 100 lashes is tied to a post and severely flogged in this Australian western. *''[[Vinegar Hill (novel)| Vinegar Hill]]'' (2005). A man has flashbacks to the [[Belting (beating)| beltings]] he received from his father. *''[[Inglourious Basterds]]'' (2009). A man's back is whipped in this WWII drama. '''2010s''' *''TimeShift: Crime and Punishment'' (2010). BBC documentary examining changing attitudes to corporal punishment in the 20th century. *''[[Six Bullets]]'' (2012). A mercenary is lashed with whips and chains. *''[[Spartacus: Vengeance]]'' (2012). Season 2, Episode 3. A man is lashed with a whip to make him reveal the whereabouts of Spartacus. *''[[The Hunger Games: Catching Fire]]'' (2013). An agitator is bound to the whipping post and flogged with a cat o'nine tails. *''[[12 Years a Slave (film)| 12 Years a Slave]]'' (2013). A man forced into slavery is beaten with a paddle and a leather belt; later he whips a man who has tried to whip him. *''[[Field Punishment No. 1 (film)|Field Punishment No. 1]]'' (2014). Military discipline known as [[Field Punishment No. 1]] is administered to New Zealand [[conscientious objectors]], including [[Archibald Baxter]] during the First World War.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3124186/ imdb]</ref> *''[[Hercules (2014 film)| Hercules]]'' (2014). A warlord is chained and lashed. *''[[Unbroken (film)| Unbroken]]'' (2014). Main character is punished by his father with a leather belt; later he endures floggings in a prisoner of war camp.
